description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting and challenging opportunity has arisen to join and lead the existing Looked After Children team Hull (CHCP). &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you interested in joining an established and supportive Looked After Children health team to expand your knowledge, skills, influence and experience in promoting the health and wellbeing in Looked After Children.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This position will require extensive experience within the looked after children specialism and some management experience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will offer high quality advice and expertise in regard to Looked After Children services in order to support the wider CHCP staff and partner agencies. You will be managing a team of looked after children&#39;s nurses advising and supporting them to deliver the service&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will need to have a commitment and passion to deliver high quality evidenced based care and support for this vulnerable group of children, including unaccompanied asylum seeking children and young people.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Named nurse will also hold a small caseload of looked after children whilst also reporting to commissioners and other agencies. We are looking for someone who has the ability to analyse information and prepare reports.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role is a high profile and essential position within Hull CHCP requiring a close and effective working relationship with the Designated Nurse for Looked After Children in NHS Hull Clinical Commissioning Group (CCG). &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you feel you have the qualities and skills required for this critical and important role we would welcome your application&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information please contact Kerah McRae on 07919544039, &lt;span&gt;email kerah.mcrae@nhs.net.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
